This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and improving the programming experience of TensorFlow, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses software engineering principles and source code transformation, which could also place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The use of staged programming and dynamic dispatch could also suggest a connection to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper's focus on improving the ease of writing machine learning code while maintaining performance could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's discussion of backend agnosticism and targeting alternate IRs could suggest a connection to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
